                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>መስተ፡ for መስተብቍዕ፡</item>
                           <item>ም፡/ምል፡, ምልጣ፡ for ምልጣን፡</item>
                           <item>ምዕራ፡ for ምዕራፍ፡</item>
                           <item>ማርያ፡ for ማርያም፡</item>
                           <item>ካ፡ for ይቤ፡ ካህን</item>
                           <item>ዲ፡ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን</item>
                           <item>ሕ፡ for ይቤ፡ ሕዝብ</item>
                           <item>ሃ፡ for ሃሌሉያ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines and one group of lines
                           (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page; two initial lines of
                           Texts I-2 to I-5; names of sections in Text I-1 (e.g., mǝʿrāf za-sänuy);
                           two initial lines of sections of Text I-4; names of feasts and other
                           occasions; names of supplications, antiphons and chants, and their
                           abbreviations (e.g., mastabqʷǝʿ, mǝqnāy, mǝlṭān, mazmur, salām, ʾaryām,
                           qǝne); initial words of supplications, antiphons and other chants, and
                           their sections (e.g., ḥǝli, yǝtbārak, sǝbḥǝwwo, gǝnäyu, täśahalänni,
                           nǝsebbǝḥo, ʾantä, täkäśtä, sǝmʿanni); musical notation: elements of
                           marginal signs; names of the three categories of melody ʿǝzl, gǝʿǝz,
                           ʾararay; directives for the ministers (e.g., ǝm-qǝdmä, wa-dǝḫrehu,
                           wa-ʾǝmzǝ, ʾǝm-lǝdät, ba-zamana); elements of the punctuation signs;
                           Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Despite the changes in the quality of
                        the handwriting the Ms. was most probably written by one scribe. <locus from="3r" to="50vb">3r-50vb</locus>: very regular, upright and slender
                        letters; <locus from="51ra" to="51vb">51ra-51vb</locus>: less regular,
                        smaller, slightly left-sloping letters; <locus from="51ra" to="59vb">51ra-59vb</locus>: very regular, broad, smaller
                        letters.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#53va">ff. 53va-54ra</locus>
                           <desc type="CalendaricNote"> Note on computus. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"> ዓለም፡ ከተፈጠረ፡ ዘመን፡
                              ከተቈጸረ፡ ፯ሽ፡ ከ፪፡ መቶ፡ ፹፬፡ ነው። በይኽን፡ በዓቢይ፡ ቀመር፡ በማዕከላይ፡ ቀመር፡ በንዑስ፡ ቀመር፡
                              ይቀምርዋል…</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic, possibly in the main hand. It
                              dates to approximately the same period as Text I. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#60r">f. 60ra-rb</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText"> Note on the grammar of Gǝʿǝz (säwasǝw). </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"> ሰዋስው፡ ብሂል፡ መስላል፡ ነው፡ ታኳ[sic]፡
                              ነው፡ ገቢርና፡ ተገብሮ፡ የሚባሉ፡ ፯፡ ናቸው…</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic, in a poor hand. It deals with the
                              verbal paradigms in Gǝʿǝz exposed in a way peculiar to the
                              säwasǝw-books. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Tamallas-signs, in the shape of a cross, indicating the
                           place where the omissions written in the margins, in the main hand,
                           belong: <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus> l.3, 10vb l.1, 11rb l.2, 12vb
                           l.9, 17ra l.16, 20vb l.4, 27vb l.2, 30vb l.31, 33va l.19, 34va l.4, 41va
                           l.3, 42rb l.16, 44va l.1, 45va l.1, 45va l.20, 46rb l.10, 48ra l.10, 50va
                           l.6; in a crude secondary hand: <locus target="#14rb">14rb</locus> l.13,
                           14vb l.8, 15rb l.19, 16ra l.20, 17ra l.2, 40ra l.2, 40ra l.18. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>
                           Corrections are written over erasures, in a secondary hand: <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>, 11ra. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Omissions are written in the
                           margin, in the main hand: <locus target="#37va">37va</locus>b, 50rab,
                           52ra; in a secondary hand 17rb, 35rb, 40ra</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc> A few words are blotted
                           out: <locus target="#47va">47va</locus>, 50rab.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>The parchment
                           guard in quire A originates from another ms. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6"><desc>Spaces for
                           rubrication are left unfilled on <locus target="#17rb">17rb</locus>,
                           17vb, 18vb, 33va. </desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e7"><desc>Scribbles: <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>,
                           2v, 32rb. 
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>, 2r.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Names of the days of the week, written in the side
                              margins in a secondary hand, indicate daily readings: ዘረብዑ: <locus target="#15ra">fol. 15ra</locus> ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#15va">fol.
                                 15va</locus> ዘአርብ: <locus target="#15vb">fol.
                           15vb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
